summary: So I just started Good Omens and
body:
So I just started Good Omens and

  • David Tennant is still a gift from God
  • Crowley is a Queen stan I’m screaming!!!!
  • I will be dancing to every Queen song that starts playing unless restrained.
  • The anti-Christ is precious and please let him bring about good (that is a sentence I hope I’ll be forgiven for)
  • Every time I see Gabriel all I can think is “John Hamm Solo”
  • David Tennant dressed as a nanny
  • If Mozart is in Hell, where are Freddie Mercury and John Lennon?
  • George Harrison???
  • (Edit: thanks for reminding me Beethoven and Bach are in Heaven)

title: Good Omens, Episode 2 Review: "The Book"
body:
Good Omens, Episode 2 Review: “The Book”

If “In The Beginning” established Crowley and Aziraphale as the stars of Good Omens, “The Book” asks what if they weren’t?

Photo Credit: Chris Raphael

OK, maybe nothing so dramatic, but it is a change from the chronological order of episode one, which seemed to indicate episode two would pick up with Adam (Sam Taylor Buck) and his friends. With Armageddon gaining on us, the show had to slow…
